               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the original donors and scribes; a few lines on the incipit page of Text II-1, incipit of all other texts; incipit of sections of Texts II-4, III and IV; the words sälam "salutation", täfäśśǝḥi "rejoice" and a few other words (fols. 19vb, 20ra, 25rb, 91rb); elements of the punctuation signs and of the text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The miracles of Mary written in hand c (40 miracles) are numbered.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text II-1 contains:</note>
                     <note>- Excerpt from the Gospel of Matthew (Mt. 25: 1-13) (fols. 21va-22rb).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text II-2 includes the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- [...] ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Maryam ʾǝmmu lä-ʾIyäsus Krǝstos kähali ... "[...] O my Lady Mary, Mother of Jesus Christ the Almighty ..." (fols. 26va-27ra)(cp. ChRep no. 373)</note>
                     <note>- Sälam läki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Maryam ʾǝmmä mädḫǝn wä-ʾǝmmä bǝrhan ... " Salutation to you, o my Lady Mary, Mother of the Saviour and Mother of the Light ..." (fols. 27ra-28ra).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Two worn paper-pictures of St. Mary and St. Joseph are sewn with textile onto fol. 15v.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus target="222rb"/>Fol. 222rb: ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘጸሐፍክዋ፡ አነ፡ ኃጥእ፡ ወልደ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ዘእንበለ፡ አስብ፡ በእንተ፡ ፍቅራ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ከመ፡ ትኩነኒ፡ መርሐ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት። ወዝኒ፡ ብራና፡ ዘወሀባ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ከመ፡ ትትወሐሶ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት። ለፍቁረ፡ ዚአሃ፡ ቀሲስ፡ ወልደ፡ ዳዊት። ኅቡረ፡ ደርገ፡ ይክፍሎሙ፡ ምስለ፡ ጻድቃን፡ ወሰማዕት፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ ዓሜን፡ ወ [fol. 222va] ዓሜን። ለዛቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘፈሐቃ፡ እምዛቲ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ወዘዐደፈ፡ ቃላቲሃ፡ ወዘተአገላ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በቃለ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ወ[በ]ቃለ፡ ዚአየሂ፡ አነ፡ ኃጥእ፡ ወልደ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ለይኩን፡ ለይኩን።<foreign xml:lang="en">Fol. 222rb: I, the sinner Wäldä Krǝstos, wrote this book without reward (but) for the sake of love to Our Lady Mary, so that it might be a guide for me to the Kingdom of Heaven. And the one who gave the parchment to Our Lady Mary is priest Wäldä Dawit, so that She might be the guarantor for her beloved one in the Kingdom of Heaven. May He reward them together like the righteous and martyrs. For ever and ever. Amen and Amen. The one who stole this book from this church or erased (its text) or demeaned its words or robbed it shall be excommunicated by the word of Peter and Paul and also by my word, of the sinful Wäldä Krǝstos. So be it. So be it.</foreign>
                        <note>This colophon is repeated in the margins of fol. 117v.</note>
                     </colophon>
