                  <handDesc><!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <ab type="script">Hand a: rather fine. Hand b: mediocre. Hand c: mediocre.</ab>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (hand a: deep reddish brown, hand b and hand c: strong red)</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" corresp="PRS00000">Wäldä Krǝstos</persName>Wäldä Krǝstos (hand a) is mentioned as the scribe in the colophon. His name is written in supplication formulas (e.g., fols. 43ra, 54rb, 101ra, 109rb, 206ra, 219va, 220rb), but has been often erased and replaced with that of Wäldä Mikaʾel.&#xD;
The name of the scribe, determined as "hand c", has been erased on fol. 204vb; only the second part, Śǝllase, is preserved. Most probably the name is ʾArʾaya Śǝllase.<date>Hand a: mid 17th - mid 18th century (?). Hand b: 19th century. Hand c: mid 17th - mid 18th century (?)</date>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand a, Wäldä Krǝstos: fols. 2ra-14rb, 25ra-117vb, 206ra-222ra; rounded, sometimes irregularly formed, slightly left-sloping letters.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic">
Hand b: fols. 16ra-23vb; broadly spaced and angular letters with short hairlines (esp. መ ወ ጽ).<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic">
Hand c: fols. 118ra-205ra, 222vb-225vb; slight italic script with forked hook vowel markers (ተ ታ ብ ኃ ዚ ጉ ያ). Some letters have short hairlines  (መ ን ኃ የ ድ ገ ጉ ጠ).<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
